[Episode Twenty-eight]

3
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:07,600
Please be quiet.

4
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:09,440
Quiet please.

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,360
Mr. Cai has arrived.

6
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:26,710
[Cai Yuanpei, styled Jiemin, President of Peking University]

7
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:42,960
Mr. Cai, and fellow classmates.

8
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,080
This demonstration on the streets today

9
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,560
was the collective decision of all of us.

10
00:00:46,835 --> 00:00:48,523
[Li Dazhao, styled Shouchang, Director of Peking University Library]

11
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:47,840
We cannot

12
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,920
leave the arrested 32 classmates

13
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:50,800
to face the consequences.

14
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:51,840
I propose

15
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,600
all the students in Peking University

16
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:54,880
must unite.

17
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,200
We go turn ourselves in to the Nine Gates Infantry Commander together.

18
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,080
We go to jail together.

19
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:01,520
We pledge to defend our arrested classmates to the death together.

20
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:04,160
We live and die with the arrested students!

21
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:06,480
We live and die with the arrested students!

22
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,120
We live and die with the arrested students!

23
00:01:10,240 --> 00:01:11,360
Everyone, quiet please.

24
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:13,600
Let's listen to what Mr. Cai has to say.

25
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:21,120
I want to tell you.

26
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,680
The more intense the situation we are facing with,

27
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:26,000
the more we need to calm down.

28
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:28,000
We are all scholars.

29
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,840
We are sensible.

30
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,760
We are rational.

31
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,360
We will never be like reckless bulls.

32
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,160
We will not do what mobs do.

33
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:38,320
I, Cai Yuanpei, fully support

34
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,160
students' patriotic actions.

35
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:42,480
But what happened

36
00:01:42,960 --> 00:01:44,320
is not what I expected.

37
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,800
I feel rather devastated now.

38
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,600
Heartbroken.

39
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,200
I am the principal, I should take the fall for this.

40
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,120
I should take the blame and resign.

41
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:58,800
But the most urgent thing now

42
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:00,640
is to do everything possible

43
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:04,480
to rescue the arrested 32 students.

44
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,440
I want them out safely.

45
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:10,080
I just got word that

46
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,760
The arrested students

47
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,080
has been transferred to the metropolitan police department.

48
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:17,120
I am yet not sure it's a good thing or not.

49
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,120
But I have made up my mind.

50
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,280
I am to go to the Metropolitan Police Department in person

51
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,520
and meet Police Chief Wu Bingxiang.

52
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,720
I am to ask him to release the students.

53
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,320
I'm going to take them back,

54
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,800
back to school safely.

55
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:34,000
So here, I ask my fellow students to be patient.

56
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,600
Do not go out.

57
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,360
I will update with you all.

58
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,000
Can everyone do that?

59
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,280
Yes.

60
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,400
Students.

61
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,920
What Mr. Cai said just now,

62
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:51,760
did everyone listen?

63
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,840
We all want to be

64
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,200
a patriotic Chinese.

65
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,120
But patriotism requires

66
00:02:57,520 --> 00:03:00,160
us to be even more calm.

67
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:02,560
Calm down.

68
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,120
Okay?

69
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:07,200
Okay.

70
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,440
This meeting decided that

71
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,280
Peking University is to be locked down.

72
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,560
Replace the principal of Peking University.

73
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,800
The arrested students are to be punished severely.

74
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,280
Wu Bingxiang, director of the Metropolitan Police Department

75
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:24,240
has put forward the plan for dealing with the arrested students.

76
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:27,520
Wu Bingxiang, Chen Zhuan and Fu Zengxiang

77
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,760
will be responsible for stopping the National Convention

78
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,760
held at Central Park on May 7th.

79
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,360
The Ministry of Education

80
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,200
will responsible for restoring school order.

81
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,520
Meeting adjourned.

82
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,400
Dismissed.

83
00:03:57,521 --> 00:03:59,949
[Qian Nengxun, styled Xicheng, Premier of the Beiyang Government]

84
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:06,240
Brother Xicheng, I resign.

85
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,680
I can't carry on

86
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,360
doing this job anymore.

87
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:17,600
Yuanshu, this is not like you.

88
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,000
You don't quit when a national disaster coming close.

89
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,600
Stay?

90
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,360
What good can I do staying?

91
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:30,320
The student demonstration was driven by their patriotism.

92
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,520
Any sensible person can see it.

93
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,760
You arrested so many students.

94
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:38,960
You also want to lock down Peking University and replace Cai Heqing.

95
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:41,680
This will not only discourage students.

96
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:44,080
Instead, it will add fuel to the fire.

97
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,120
It is bound to lead to greater chaos.

98
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:50,400
I am not drowning with you.

99
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:56,480
Yuanshu, come.

100
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:57,920
Come on.

101
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:04,000
You really don't understand my mind?

102
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,840
I have the same opinion as yours.

103
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:11,520
But can you go against Duan Qirui's will?

104
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:13,840
Students burnt down Zhaojialou

105
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,360
and wounded Zhang Zongxiang.

106
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:18,320
Xu Shuzheng threatened to set up a cannon at Jingshan.

107
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,520
He wants to erase Peking University once for all.

108
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,360
Under these circumstances,

109
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,680
some actions are necessary

110
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,240
so that everyone will agree to take a step back.

111
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,360
You want to replace Cai Yuanpei.

112
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,920
Who will be that replacement?

113
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,920
Duan Qirui nominated Ma Qichang.

114
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,920
I beat about the bush.

115
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,040
Let's make a gesture first.

116
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:41,600
Wait for things to calm down.

117
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,440
With Peking University now,

118
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,520
I think no one except Cai Yuanpei

119
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,960
can have it under control.

120
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,280
The real question here is

121
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:52,160
the police arrested dozens of students.

122
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,160
That's the tricky part.

123
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:59,120
If they don't let the students go or something goes wrong,

124
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,360
it will be a big deal.

125
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,000
We can't afford that happening.

126
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,040
Student affairs is very difficult.

127
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:11,040
The Anfu Club unanimously demanded severe punishment.

128
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,520
Only Wu Bingxiang is smart on this incident.

129
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:15,440
He intends to make use of these students,

130
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,120
so that he can have Cai Yuanpei under his thumb

131
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,120
and break down the student union.

132
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:22,320
He asked for my full cooperation too.

133
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,000
But Wu Bingxiang

134
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,360
is Duan Qirui's loyal clique.

135
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,200
Can you really trust him?

136
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,120
It is his duty after all.

137
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,680
To maintain public order in the capital,

138
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,280
you can't offend the students.

139
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,360
If this matter gets out of hand,

140
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,240
he is the first to be held accountable.

141
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,400
I say

142
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,440
the situation is hanging by a thread.

143
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,760
It's like walking a tightrope.

144
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,520
We just do what we can.

145
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,200
In the worst case scenario,

146
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,720
I resign with you.

147
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,120
These students,

148
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,920
all they do is causing troubles and making a fuss.

149
00:07:06,090 --> 00:07:09,147
[Li Changtai, Nine Gates Infantry Commander]

150
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,000
Arrest them when needed is the only way.

151
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,080
All you know is arrest.

152
00:07:10,594 --> 00:07:12,184
[Wu Bingxiang, Chief of Metropolitan Police]

153
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,520
Do you know about anything else?

154
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,920
We can't go soft on them.

155
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,360
Principal Cai, what do you want?

156
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,720
Please don't make it difficult for me.

157
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:19,920
Principal Cai, principal Cai.

158
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,360
Don't be like this please.

159
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,320
Principal Cai, principal Cai.

160
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,520
What are you doing, let him go!

161
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:24,400
Cheif, he-

162
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:26,480
he just broke in.

163
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:27,840
Leave.

164
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:28,160
Yes.

165
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,440
Cai Yuanpei.

166
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,000
How dare you come here.

167
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,840
What did you do to manage-

168
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,080
Stop!

169
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:49,280
Principal Cai, what can I do for you?

170
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:52,560
I am here for the 32 students

171
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,200
you arrested.

172
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,400
I would like to ask the Chief of Metropolitan Police

173
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,000
and the Nine Gates Infantry Commander.

174
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,600
Let my students go.

175
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:04,800
I'll take all the responsibility.

176
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,560
Release them?

177
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,800
I say I should arrest you too!

178
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,360
If you let my students go,

179
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:12,880
you can arrest me.

180
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,440
Principal Cai, you are exaggerating.

181
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,280
The two of us here

182
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:21,120
were scolded by President Xu today.

183
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,480
Bad mood.

184
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,520
Don't take it seriously.

185
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:26,080
But what you asked for

186
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,840
is not within our power to decide.

187
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:30,160
We're just running errands here.

188
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:33,440
Unless there is an order from the president, we can't do anything.

189
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,000
I understand, Chief Wu.

190
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,600
I will go visit the President.

191
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,560
And I will not ask too much of you two.

192
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,400
Only for tonight,

193
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:45,040
I would like to ask you two to do me a favor.

194
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:48,240
Let me take my students back tonight.

195
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,600
I will for sure go visit President Xu tomorrow.

196
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,400
I will resign

197
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,480
if that's what it costs.

198
00:08:57,040 --> 00:09:00,400
You are making a laugh, the President of Peking University.

199
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,560
Are you now treating the law and regulations as a joke?

200
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,480
What a joke.

201
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,840
These students of yours,

202
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,680
now they are prisoners of the state.

203
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:13,840
Sir,

204
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,800
I am Cai Yuanpei, a teacher.

205
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:19,120
Now my students are in trouble.

206
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,640
It is my obligation to save them.

207
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,400
It is my obligation to care.

208
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:25,120
So I'd like to sincerely ask two of you,

209
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:27,760
do me a favor please.

210
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,280
Don't you two have kids?

211
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,600
Don't your children go to school to study?

212
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:35,600
General Li said that the students commited crime.

213
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,280
I would like to ask

214
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,560
did students act for themselves?

215
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,160
They did it for they have patriotic hearts.

216
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,280
They did it

217
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,960
for fighting the unfair Paris Peace Treaty.

218
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,560
This unfair Paris peace treaty

219
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,960
aroused the anger of every Chinese.

220
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,800
You two

221
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:53,840
are public officials of the government of the Republic of China.

222
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,200
In your eyes,

223
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,680
somehow patriotic students equals to prisoners.

224
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:10,160
Jieping, what Principal Cai just said-

225
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:17,920
Right or wrong is none of my business.

226
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,200
Cai Yuanpei.

227
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:21,360
They say you are untouchable.

228
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,920
I'm going to teach you a lesson today.

229
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,320
Let you know what the rules are.

230
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,240
Get him out of here.

231
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,120
His students are nothing but trouble makers

232
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,240
act against the rule.

233
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,840
I will arrest and kill them if needed!

234
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,280
Take him away, go take a rest.

235
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,320
I am touching you today!

236
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,640
Principal Cai, you saw it.

237
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:41,840
Only if

238
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,400
there are orders from President Xu.

239
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:45,120
Otherwise,

240
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,000
there's really nothing we can do.

241
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,920
Let's take it slow.

242
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:50,560
Chief Wu.

243
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:50,960
Take it slow.

244
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,840
What is he doing...

245
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:54,960
Chief Wu!

246
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,120
China is the Chinese people's China.

247
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,040
You are also Chinese.

248
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:07,120
We marched in the streets for China.

249
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:10,400
What's wrong with that?

250
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:15,680
We are trying to make the government

251
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,040
refuse to sign the Paris Peace Treaty

252
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,320
If Shandong is gone,

253
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,480
will China still be there?

254
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,080
That's right!

255
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,440
Independence or death!

256
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,840
Independence or death!

257
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:30,240
Independence or death!

258
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:32,640
Independence or death!

259
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:34,400
Be quiet. This is a prison.

260
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,000
No matter who you are out there.

261
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:36,720
In here,

262
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,080
you have to follow the rules.

263
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:41,360
Prisoners are not allowed to talk and play with each other.

264
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,200
When sleeping,

265
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:46,560
everyone must either look up or turn around

266
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,080
every half hour.

267
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,000
To prove that the prisoner is still alive.

268
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,720
Prisoners can pee in the urinal.

269
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,960
For the other one they must hold it in.

270
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,480
This is a violation of our human rights.

271
00:11:58,400 --> 00:11:59,760
You have to follow the rules here.

272
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,680
You can wait until tomorrow noon

273
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:02,560
to defecate!

274
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:04,000
You are violating our human rights.

275
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:04,880
I protest!

276
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:06,800
Yes, we protest!

277
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:10,240
Protest! Protest! Protest!

278
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,920
Protest as you like.

279
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:13,840
But the rules must be enforced.

280
